1 0 0 1 50 780 Tm (MediSphere Privacy Policy \(Sample\)) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 766 Tm (Last Updated: 2026-04-01) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 752 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 738 Tm (1. About MediSphere) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 724 Tm (MediSphere Health Technologies Private Limited \("MediSphere", "we", "our", "us"\) provides) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 710 Tm (telemedicine consultations, digital health record management, diagnostics coordination, and) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 696 Tm (chronic care support.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 682 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 668 Tm (2. Information we collect) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 654 Tm (We collect account data \(name, email, phone\), patient demographics, clinical records) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 640 Tm (\(diagnosis, prescriptions, lab summaries\), teleconsultation metadata and communications,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 626 Tm (insurance and billing data, device/security logs, and emergency contact information.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 612 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 598 Tm (3. Why we process this information) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 584 Tm (We process data to deliver healthcare services, schedule and conduct consultations, support) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 570 Tm (clinical decision-making, coordinate diagnostics/pharmacy services, process claims and) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 556 Tm (payments, detect fraud, and meet legal and medical record obligations.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 542 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 528 Tm (4. Consent and lawful processing) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 514 Tm (We seek informed consent where required and provide clear notice about processing purposes.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 500 Tm (You may withdraw consent for optional processing \(for example, promotional communications\) at) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 486 Tm (any time.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 472 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 458 Tm (5. Sharing of personal data) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 444 Tm (We may share data with treating doctors, labs, pharmacies, insurance TPAs, payment processors,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 430 Tm (cloud and security vendors, and regulators where legally required.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 416 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 402 Tm (6. Cross-border processing) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 388 Tm (Some infrastructure and specialist support providers may process data outside India. We apply) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 374 Tm (contractual safeguards and comply with applicable Indian data transfer restrictions.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 360 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 346 Tm (7. Data principal rights) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 332 Tm (You may request access, correction, update, and erasure of your personal data, subject to) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 318 Tm (applicable medical retention laws and legitimate legal obligations.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 304 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 290 Tm (8. Security safeguards) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 276 Tm (We apply encryption in transit and at rest, role-based access controls, audit logging, multi-) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 262 Tm (factor authentication, periodic vulnerability assessments, and incident response procedures.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 248 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 234 Tm (9. Data retention) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 220 Tm (We retain medical and transaction records for periods required by applicable healthcare,) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 206 Tm (insurance, and taxation laws. Data is deleted or anonymized once no longer required.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 192 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 178 Tm (10. Children's and sensitive health data) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 164 Tm (Where child patient data is processed, parent or guardian-driven workflows are applied.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 150 Tm (Sensitive health and biometric-related data is handled with enhanced safeguards and restricted) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 136 Tm (access.) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 122 Tm () Tj
1 0 0 1 50 108 Tm (11. Contact and grievance) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 94 Tm (Privacy Contact: privacy@medisphere.in) Tj
1 0 0 1 50 80 Tm (Grievance Officer: grievance@medisphere.in) Tj
